***Sidenote***: from the perspective of object-oriented design, this functionality can be encapsulated in a *class*, let&#39;s say `MatrixStatistics`. That will allow you to store these data, and might be something like element count, or histogram of frequencies for each subarray inside an **object**. Which can be returned from a method (*as you know, it&#39;s not possible to return multiple values from the method*), or used as a field. As an example from the JDK of such a mutable object caring statistical data, you might take a look at [`IntSummaryStatistics`](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/util/IntSummaryStatistics.html) class.

